main event: An object resembling a second magnitude star was observed moving in a southeastern direction over the Pacific Ocean for 11 minutes.
interesting points: The object was first sighted by a duty lookout and confirmed by another observer., The object had a brightness similar to a star and was observed at an elevation of 66 degrees., It disappeared at a bearing of 132 degrees on the horizon., Air and surface radar were unable to detect the object., The observation conforms to the pattern of satellite activity.
sighted object: an object resembling a second magnitude star
